text: Or maybe they will meet in Hell someday, two 1982 Subaru Brats parked out in front of a Denny's, Ray eating at some chicken strips with mixed barbeque-mayo sauce while Blister talks about how much of a douche Lucifer is. Todd is talking on his three-nutsack cellphone to crank call the living. Teodor is outside doing parkour. In comes Ramses Luther with this hell of drawn look at Ray. He just stands there, arms crossed. "Boy," he'd say, "You beat the rules 'til its blood run." He'd just fix his eye all steady, no sense of what he thinks, then stone cold walks out and vanishes into the far reaches of Hell, never seen again by the devil or god itself.
